# Railway Deploy Requirements

## Dockerfile

- Base image: `node:20-bookworm-slim`
- MUST install openssl before Prisma generate: `RUN apt-get update -y && apt-get install -y openssl && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*`
- Without openssl, Prisma cannot establish SSL connections to Supabase and the app fails at startup (wait-for-db retries 30x then exits)
- CMD runs: `wait-for-db.js` → `prisma db push` → `node dist/server.js`

## Prisma Schema

- Generator MUST include `binaryTargets = ["native", "debian-openssl-3.0.x"]` for the Debian container
- Without this, Prisma defaults to openssl-1.1.x which doesn't match the bookworm-slim image

## Environment

- DATABASE_URL on Railway points to Supabase (pooler, SSL required)
- Local .env uses localhost — never commit local DB URLs to Railway
- Storage paths use `/app/storage` (Railway volume mount), not `./uploads`

## Common Deploy Failures

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---------|-------|-----|
| wait-for-db retries 30x | Missing openssl in Docker | Add `apt-get install -y openssl` step |
| Prisma "failed to detect libssl" | Wrong/missing binaryTargets | Add `debian-openssl-3.0.x` to schema |
| Build exit 137 (OOM) | Railpack apt step | Use custom Dockerfile instead of Railpack |
| OpenAI crash on startup | Missing OPENAI_API_KEY | Use lazy init pattern in ai.service.ts |
